<plot>"Fyra små filmer" ("Four are four individual films. The first one "Gunnar Rehlin - en liten film om att göra någon illa" (in English: "Gunnar Rehlin - a short film about hurting somebody" is a made as an episode of the American documentary series "Insight". It's about The Killing gang's advertising campaign against film critic Gunnar Rehlin. The second is "Ben &amp; Gunnar - en liten film om manlig vänskap" ("Ben &amp; Gunnar - a short film about male friendship"). It is a parody of "When Harry Met Sally..." The summer of 1985 Ben and Gunnar get to know each other during a car trip to Göteborg to see Bruce Springsteen on Ullevi. Five years later they meet again. The third episode is "På sista versen - en liten film om döden" (Almost at the end - a short film about death"). About the director KG Forsberg, who together with photographer Tommy Bohlin, are making a documentary about his father who is dying. His bosses at SVT are enthusiastic about the project. Until his father, to everybody's vexation, starts getting better. The fourth episode is "Torsk på Tallinn - en liten film om ensamhet" ("Cod (or John) on Tallinn - a short film about loneliness"). It's filmed as a documentary about a couple of Swedish men who participate in an arranged (by Percy Nilegård) trip to Tallinn to find a wife.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?177515</url></doc>
